                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/stripe/edit/master/knpu/ep1-charging/centralize-stripe-code.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Stripe's API is really organized. Our code that <em>talks</em> to it is getting a little
crazy, unless you like long, procedural code that you can't re-use. Please tell me
that's not the case.</p>
<p>Let's get this organized! At the very least, we should do this because eventually
we're going to need to re-use some of this logic - particularly with subscriptions.</p>
<p>Here's the goal of the next few minutes: move each <em>thing</em> we're doing in the controller
into a set of nice, re-usable functions. To do that, inside AppBundle, create a new
class called <code>StripeClient</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="d425d3acda">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-9" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            9 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="src/AppBundle/StripeClient.php">src/AppBundle/StripeClient.php</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
