<p>Thanks to auto-wiring, Symfony will pass the <code>stripe_secret_key</code> parameter as
the first argument, but then autowire the second, <code>EntityManager</code> argument.</p>
<p>The end-result is this: when our <code>StripeClient</code> object is created, the API key is
set immediately.</p>
<h2 id="moving-invoice-logic">Moving Invoice Logic <a class="headerlink" href="centralize-stripe-code#moving-invoice-logic" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Ok, the hard stuff is behind us: let's move the last two pieces of logic: creating
an <code>InvoiceItem</code> and creating an <code>Invoice</code>. In <code>StripeClient</code>, add
<code>public function createInvoiceItem()</code> with an <code>$amount</code> argument, the <code>$user</code> to
attach it to and a <code>$description</code>:</p>
